   Beryllium Technology

   Rich Castro, MST-6

   Principal Investigator


   Technology work at Los Alamos includes the development and testing of
   radiation-resistant ceramics for insulators and diagnostic components
   and the beryllium-spray technology for coating the surfaces of
   plasma-facing components in the International Thermonuclear
   Experimental Reactor.
